1
00:00:30,764 --> 00:00:34,063
<i>[Surf Crashing]</i>

2
00:00:37,003 --> 00:00:39,995
<i>[Seagulls Squawking]</i>

3
00:00:41,908 --> 00:00:46,971
<i>- [Man Shouting In German]
- [Crowd Cheering]</i>

4
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:50,607
<i>[Man] The army has recruited the Spanish
colonial army of Morocco.</i>

5
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,582
<i>[Crowd Shouting In Foreign Language]</i>

6
00:00:52,685 --> 00:00:54,915
<i>[Man] This is an announcement
from your government.</i>

7
00:00:55,021 --> 00:00:57,216
<i>There has been a military uprising.</i>

8
00:00:57,323 --> 00:01:00,724
<i>- [Man Speaking Foreign Language]
- [Airplane Engines Roaring]</i>

9
00:01:04,631 --> 00:01:07,794
<i>[Man #1]
One, two. One, two. One, two.</i>

10
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,300
<i>[Man #2]
Surrender.</i>

11
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:10,960
<i>- [Man #3] Ready.
- Surrender.</i>

12
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:13,062
<i>[Man #3]
Aim. Firel</i>

13
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:17,075
<i>- [Gunshot]
- [Airplane Engine Roaring]</i>

14
00:01:53,346 --> 00:01:54,370
[Church Bells Tolling]

15
00:01:56,149 --> 00:01:59,550
- [Birds Chirping]
- [Horn Honking]

16
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:03,456
<i>[Man Narrating]
I was a war baby.</i>

17
00:02:04,657 --> 00:02:06,625
<i>But luckily for me, I haven't had to fight...</i>

18
00:02:06,726 --> 00:02:11,129
<i>in any of the 165 wars
that have occurred in my lifetime.</i>

19
00:02:12,165 --> 00:02:14,531
<i>My father wasn't so lucky.</i>

20
00:02:15,835 --> 00:02:17,462
<i>When he was a young man...</i>

21
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:20,767
<i>everyone in Spain had
to take sides and take up arms.</i>

22
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:24,275
<i>The decision may have taken a second...</i>

23
00:02:24,377 --> 00:02:27,744
<i>but the consequences
lasted the rest of his life.</i>

24
00:02:29,048 --> 00:02:31,642
<i>He never talked about the war...</i>

25
00:02:31,751 --> 00:02:35,278
<i>until I was asked to write a book
about a dead priest-</i>

26
00:02:35,388 --> 00:02:37,583
<i>Josemaría Escrivá.</i>

27
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:41,922
<i>And then he began to talk and talk and talk.</i>

28
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:48,597
<i>And that's how I went looking for a saint
and found my father instead.</i>

29
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:54,840
<i>I think it was Oscar Wilde who wrote...</i>

30
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:57,136
<i>"Every saint has a past...</i>

31
00:02:57,243 --> 00:03:00,303
<i>and every sinner has a future. "</i>

32
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:08,612
Josemaría!

33
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:10,814
It's the Father. Quick!

34
00:03:10,924 --> 00:03:12,892
Quick! Get the doctor!

35
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:27,138
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

36
00:03:32,812 --> 00:03:34,837
[Man]
In June of 1976...

37
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:37,416
the nun was at the point of death...

38
00:03:37,517 --> 00:03:42,955
diagnosed with a multiple
calcific lipomatosis tumor, causing pain...

39
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:48,619
attaining a mass the size of an orange
on the left shoulder.

40
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:52,494
Cured in a sudden and lasting way...

41
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:58,504
after the Servant of God,
Josemaría Escrivá...

42
00:03:58,605 --> 00:04:01,301
had been invoked.

43
00:04:05,211 --> 00:04:07,202
[Phone Ringing]

44
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:11,047
- [Ringing]
- [Machine Clicks, Beeps]

45
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,550
<i>[Man]
You have reached Judge Manolo Torres.</i>

46
00:04:13,653 --> 00:04:16,747
<i>- Leave a message.
- [Beeps]</i>

47
00:04:16,856 --> 00:04:20,883
<i>Dad? It's- It's me, Robert.</i>

48
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:22,757
<i>Your son.</i>

49
00:04:22,862 --> 00:04:24,557
<i>I'm in Rome.</i>

50
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:27,224
<i>I'm doing a book on Josemaría Escrivá.</i>

51
00:04:28,201 --> 00:04:30,761
<i>I'm- I'm coming to Madrid, Dad...</i>

52
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:34,704
<i>and, you know, I-I want
to talk to you about him.</i>

53
00:04:34,807 --> 00:04:36,206
<i>Are you there?</i>

54
00:04:36,309 --> 00:04:39,107
<i>Please, Dad, pick up the phone.</i>

55
00:04:41,214 --> 00:04:44,411
<i>Okay. Well, I'll call you when I arrive.</i>

56
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:46,212
[Machine Clicks]

57
00:04:48,888 --> 00:04:51,516
And why this interest in Escrivá?

58
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:57,256
The uproar in the press about his possible
canonization turned my publisher on.

59
00:04:58,531 --> 00:05:01,159
You know, and curiously, he-

60
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,792
he came from the same town as my father.

61
00:05:03,903 --> 00:05:07,566
Ah, yes, of course.
How is the judge, Roberto?

62
00:05:07,674 --> 00:05:09,938
To be honest, l-
[Clears Throat]

63
00:05:10,043 --> 00:05:11,943
We haven't spoken in...

64
00:05:12,045 --> 00:05:13,808
eight years.

65
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:18,612
So I moved to London permanently,
and since then-

66
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:21,414
Well, he's not very forgiving,
my father.

67
00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:22,988
Eight years, huh?

68
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:25,080
- Children?
- No.

69
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:27,318
I don't quite see myself as a father.

70
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:28,792
[Chuckles]

71
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:31,056
Your father is a product of difficult times.

72
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,132
You should try to understand him.

73
00:05:33,232 --> 00:05:35,826
Well, I do, Monsignor. I do.

74
00:05:35,935 --> 00:05:38,369
God bless you in your quest.

75
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:40,939
- And give my regards to, uh-
- To Leila.

76
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,008
Leila.

77
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:44,940
- Good-bye.
- Good-bye.

78
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:54,548
- [Robert] Are you sure?
- Yes.

79
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:59,215
That's Josemaría Escrivá in the middle.

80
00:05:59,325 --> 00:06:01,691
And that's me on the right.

81
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:04,695
And on the left, your father.

82
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:08,801
Here's another one. At the seminary.

83
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:12,434
<i>- [Phone Rings]
- [Line Clicks]</i>

84
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:13,971
<i>[Manolo]
Hello.</i>

85
00:06:14,073 --> 00:06:16,439
Dad. I'm in Madrid.

86
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:17,975
Been a long time.

87
00:06:18,077 --> 00:06:22,480
Listen. I'm close to the apartment,
and I wanted to come see you.

88
00:06:22,582 --> 00:06:24,812
Why would you write a book about him?

89
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:27,078
That's what I wanted to talk to you about.

90
00:06:27,186 --> 00:06:29,086
Leave it alone, Roberto.

91
00:06:29,188 --> 00:06:31,622
<i>Well, I found out that you were
in the seminary with him...</i>

92
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:34,420
and you never told me
that you wanted to be a priest.

93
00:06:34,527 --> 00:06:37,894
<i>- Don't you think that's weird?
- Yes, I thought so too.</i>

94
00:06:37,997 --> 00:06:40,329
That's why I left after a year, Roberto.

95
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:43,061
Why? Was it because of the civil war?

96
00:06:43,169 --> 00:06:44,864
<i>- [Gasps]
- [Line Clicks]</i>

97
00:06:44,971 --> 00:06:46,768
<i>[Dial Tone]</i>

98
00:07:00,653 --> 00:07:02,621
<i>[Woman]
Hello. London University.</i>

99
00:07:02,722 --> 00:07:05,020
Dr. Leila Azoulay, please.

100
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:06,682
<i>Which department?</i>

101
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:08,818
Mathematical Physics.

102
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,453
Good timing.
I was just about to call you.

103
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:13,191
<i>How's Spain?</i>

104
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:14,698
I love Spain.

105
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:16,860
<i>How's your father?</i>

106
00:07:16,969 --> 00:07:18,834
I love Spain.

107
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,364
<i>Tell me.</i>

108
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:25,501
He doesn't want me to do
this Josemaría Escrivá thing.

109
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:28,102
At least you two spoke. That's progress, no?

110
00:07:28,214 --> 00:07:30,808
He knows something about Josemaría, damn it.

111
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:34,546
I know he does. Why can't he just tell me?

112
00:07:34,654 --> 00:07:38,021
I could wrangle the weekend away.

113
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,684
Want me to come out?

114
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:42,792
[Hinges Squeak]

115
00:07:55,408 --> 00:07:56,875
[Woman Screams]

116
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:10,019
[Grunting]

117
00:08:10,122 --> 00:08:12,249
[Sighs, Panting]
Gun.

118
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:24,733
No!

119
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,707
Damn it.

120
00:08:30,943 --> 00:08:32,069
[Groans]

121
00:08:33,379 --> 00:08:34,846
[Groans]

122
00:08:36,782 --> 00:08:39,717
[Groaning]

123
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:44,750
[Keys Jingling]

124
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,654
[Lock Clicks]

125
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:09,371
[Clears Throat]

126
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:14,146
I was nine
when Josemaría's path crossed mine.

127
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:17,755
<i>A long time ago.</i>

128
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:22,385
<i>Roberto, you've often told me
that I was a terrible father.</i>

129
00:09:22,495 --> 00:09:25,430
<i>What I've never told you
is that I agree with you.</i>

130
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:29,490
<i>- Manolo! Manolo!
- There's so much I haven't
told you that you need to know.</i>

131
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:32,162
<i>- So if you want to hear about the past...
- Manolo!</i>

132
00:09:32,271 --> 00:09:33,670
<i>- I'll tell you.
- Manolo!</i>

133
00:09:33,773 --> 00:09:37,800
<i>- But I warn you, there be dragons.
- Manolo! Manolo!</i>

134
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,775
Are you okay? Manolo!

135
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:41,278
- Manolo!
- [Shouts]

136
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:43,177
[Gasps]
You got me.

137
00:09:43,282 --> 00:09:46,080
<i>- I got you, Josemaría.
- I was a little terror like most boys.</i>

138
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:49,018
<i>- I'm gonna get you.
- Josemaría was no saint either.</i>

139
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:51,351
<i>There was one day he almost killed me.</i>

140
00:09:51,457 --> 00:09:52,822
[Horse Whinnying]

141
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:54,593
[Woman Shrieks]

142
00:09:54,694 --> 00:09:57,822
Good driving, boy. Come on!

143
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,558
[Yelling]

144
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,964
[Woman Shrieking]

145
00:10:03,069 --> 00:10:06,766
[Chattering]

146
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:17,677
Feels like a Taurus, Manolo.
Faster!

147
00:10:21,654 --> 00:10:22,643
[Screams]

148
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:27,487
Stop!

149
00:10:27,593 --> 00:10:30,619
- Manolo, are you all right?
- Are you mad?

150
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:34,188
Josemaría, I'll speak to your father.
He should give you a beating.

151
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,894
<i>I hate this backwater.</i>

152
00:10:37,003 --> 00:10:40,530
I've half a mind to sell up
and go back to Madrid, I promise.

153
00:10:42,008 --> 00:10:44,909
- Can I drive again, Papa?
- No, Manolo. Enough.

154
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:57,986
[Children Chattering, Laughing]

155
00:10:58,090 --> 00:11:00,752
[Barking]

156
00:11:03,295 --> 00:11:05,422
[Woman]
Here is the first one.

157
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:09,100
See?

158
00:11:09,201 --> 00:11:12,796
There are many kinds of dragons
you will have to face.

159
00:11:12,905 --> 00:11:14,532
She scares me.

160
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,200
Don't be scared, Manolo.

161
00:11:17,309 --> 00:11:20,210
How many dragons are there, Abileyza?

162
00:11:20,312 --> 00:11:22,075
Many, Josemaría.

163
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:25,776
But what matters is how you face them,
as you shall see.

164
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:29,321
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría's nanny talked about dragons...</i>

165
00:11:29,422 --> 00:11:31,754
<i>as if they really existed.</i>

166
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:36,794
<i>A quarter of a century passed
before I realized she was right.</i>

167
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:40,625
<i>But things happened in Josemaría's life...</i>

168
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:44,669
<i>that meant he understood this before I did.</i>

169
00:11:47,807 --> 00:11:51,174
[Woman Sobbing]
Why?

170
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:55,744
No!

171
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:57,748
No!

172
00:11:57,850 --> 00:12:00,819
[Sobbing Continues]

173
00:12:08,127 --> 00:12:10,595
My baby! Why?

174
00:12:43,129 --> 00:12:45,723
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría lost three sisters.</i>

175
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:49,200
<i>I lost a baby brother.</i>

176
00:12:49,301 --> 00:12:51,929
<i>In those days, death was part of life.</i>

177
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,777
[Josemaría]
Mama?

178
00:13:06,819 --> 00:13:09,117
Do you hate God now?

179
00:13:09,221 --> 00:13:11,587
No, dearest.

180
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:19,689
I... love him very much.

181
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:23,699
Will you hate him when he takes me away?

182
00:13:25,838 --> 00:13:27,328
Come here.

183
00:13:46,058 --> 00:13:48,322
I'm sorry about your sister.

184
00:13:48,427 --> 00:13:52,727
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Josemaría's father owned a chocolate factory.</i>

185
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:56,097
<i>The manager was a strange, old guy-</i>

186
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:57,669
<i>Honorio.</i>

187
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:59,829
We know we like what's here.

188
00:13:59,939 --> 00:14:02,305
We know that we want what's here.

189
00:14:02,408 --> 00:14:05,070
But what is here exactly?

190
00:14:05,177 --> 00:14:09,238
Just sit this on your tongue...

191
00:14:11,317 --> 00:14:13,046
for five seconds.

192
00:14:15,588 --> 00:14:18,148
Hmm? Now, chew...

193
00:14:18,257 --> 00:14:19,724
three times.

194
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,389
Manolo, you taste what?

195
00:14:27,499 --> 00:14:29,296
Almond.

196
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:31,062
Almond?

197
00:14:34,740 --> 00:14:35,729
Cinnamon.

198
00:14:35,841 --> 00:14:36,865
Cinnamon?

199
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:39,307
Don't scoff.

200
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:42,309
Yes. Cinnamon.

201
00:14:43,082 --> 00:14:45,482
All right, off you go.

202
00:14:45,584 --> 00:14:47,552
Josemaría, you stay here.

203
00:14:53,993 --> 00:14:58,794
I scolded Manolo for mocking
what he can't experience...

204
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:02,527
not because he couldn't experience it.

205
00:15:02,635 --> 00:15:05,536
Ah, now, look at this.

206
00:15:05,638 --> 00:15:07,230
Ugly, isn't it?

207
00:15:07,339 --> 00:15:10,331
Just a poor, ordinary little bean.

208
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:13,444
Yet, patience...

209
00:15:13,545 --> 00:15:17,743
skill, hard work and love...

210
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:22,253
can unleash the divine flavors
hidden within.

211
00:15:22,354 --> 00:15:23,821
There.

212
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:28,021
Do you understand the lesson?

213
00:15:30,362 --> 00:15:34,093
But not everyone has a taste
for the divine, you know.

214
00:15:36,068 --> 00:15:38,298
And why is that, I wonder?

215
00:15:41,473 --> 00:15:42,872
Manolo!

216
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:45,466
Manolo! Wait for me!

217
00:15:45,577 --> 00:15:47,067
Stop! Manolo!

218
00:15:47,179 --> 00:15:49,204
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
My favorite trick in those days...</i>

219
00:15:49,315 --> 00:15:52,443
<i>was stealing Josemaría's dad's chocolates.</i>

220
00:15:52,551 --> 00:15:56,681
<i>But then his dad went bankrupt
and lost the chocolate factory.</i>

221
00:15:56,789 --> 00:16:01,089
<i>And I wasn't allowed to play
with Josemaría anymore.</i>

222
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:04,060
<i>My dad thought poverty was contagious.</i>

223
00:16:04,163 --> 00:16:06,188
<i>- He said that Josemaría wasn't one of us.
- [Father] One!</i>

224
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:07,697
- [Groans]
- Two!

225
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:11,236
<i>- And my dad could be quite persuasive.
- Three!</i>

226
00:16:11,337 --> 00:16:12,429
[Groans]

227
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,340
<i>My dad had more money...</i>

228
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:20,105
<i>more cars, more houses.</i>

229
00:16:20,212 --> 00:16:23,238
<i>But Josemaría had more dad.</i>

230
00:16:24,249 --> 00:16:27,480
<i>A seed of envy began to grow in me.</i>

231
00:16:27,586 --> 00:16:30,646
<i>In a child's heart, many seeds are planted.</i>

232
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:32,986
<i>You never quite know what will grow.</i>

233
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:41,389
Hmm. I'm sure he didn't see us.

234
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:50,837
[Door Squeaks]

235
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:10,017
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

236
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:39,383
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Around that time, Josemaría changed.</i>

237
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,722
<i>I'll tell you the story as he told it to me.</i>

238
00:17:46,331 --> 00:17:49,300
<i>One cold winter night...</i>

239
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:54,270
<i>Josemaría saw footprints
in the snow outside his house.</i>

240
00:17:54,973 --> 00:17:57,373
<i>He followed them.</i>

241
00:17:57,476 --> 00:17:59,876
<i>And then he saw someone.</i>

242
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:43,516
<i>And he felt that God was calling him.</i>

243
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:05,269
<i>It wasn't unusual in those days...</i>

244
00:19:05,377 --> 00:19:08,403
<i>for a young man to want to become a priest.</i>

245
00:19:15,187 --> 00:19:19,123
<i>Like it or not, most young men were celibate.</i>

246
00:19:21,894 --> 00:19:23,987
<i>At least as a priest...</i>

247
00:19:24,096 --> 00:19:26,326
<i>you got paid for it.</i>

248
00:19:26,431 --> 00:19:29,423
<i>The priesthood was a career option.</i>

249
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:34,370
<i>But for Josemaría, it was a sacred calling.</i>

250
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:48,409
[Church Bells Tolling]

251
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:55,790
[Women Chattering]

252
00:19:57,763 --> 00:19:59,663
<i>- [Woman #1] You are incorrigible.
- [Woman #2 Chuckles]</i>

253
00:20:03,302 --> 00:20:05,896
Do you know what you're taking on, Son?

254
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:07,028
Yes, Papa.

255
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:09,505
No one to love.

256
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:11,906
Human love, I mean.

257
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:14,035
No family of your own.

258
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:17,207
<i>- No sons.
- I know, papi.</i>

259
00:20:20,085 --> 00:20:23,885
And... is this the wisest time
to become a priest?

260
00:20:26,258 --> 00:20:27,885
Probably not.

261
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:33,258
Is your father still selling
underpants, Josemaría?

262
00:20:33,365 --> 00:20:35,458
[Josemaría]
Backstabber.

263
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,660
Hey, careerist.

264
00:20:37,769 --> 00:20:40,169
- [Man] Fight! Fight!
- [Manolo] You vain little pig!

265
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,238
[Men Chanting]
Fight! Fight!

266
00:20:46,378 --> 00:20:49,905
Fight! Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

267
00:20:50,015 --> 00:20:51,846
[Whistle Blows]

268
00:20:55,354 --> 00:20:57,652
What lesson do you draw from this?

269
00:20:58,890 --> 00:21:01,916
[Clears Throat]
To control my temper.

270
00:21:02,027 --> 00:21:03,585
Bravo.

271
00:21:06,198 --> 00:21:09,861
Torres, what did you call Seminarian Escrivá?

272
00:21:09,968 --> 00:21:11,526
[Clears Throat]

273
00:21:11,637 --> 00:21:14,504
A vain little... pig.

274
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:16,506
And you- what did you call Torres?

275
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:18,667
A backstabbing careerist.

276
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:21,177
Sorry, Monsignor. I can't stand his type.

277
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:24,010
A backstabbing careerist.

278
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:26,414
That sums him up, eh?

279
00:21:26,518 --> 00:21:29,453
What, his father is rich, so he thinks
he can act like a pain in the ass?

280
00:21:29,554 --> 00:21:32,785
That's not the summing up
I had in mind, Escrivá.

281
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:37,895
Yet, isn't someone else his Father?

282
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:39,624
And yours?

283
00:21:44,903 --> 00:21:47,565
Remember, the withholding of forgiveness...

284
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:50,335
is the one thing, as our Lord made clear...

285
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:54,369
that will not be forgiven.

286
00:21:56,915 --> 00:21:58,405
So...

287
00:21:59,885 --> 00:22:02,615
do you think that two hotheads,
a hypocrite and a loser...

288
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:04,382
can be good priests?

289
00:22:07,359 --> 00:22:09,486
Well, I think it's possible.

290
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,028
I really do.

291
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:17,764
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
Well, he was wrong about me.</i>

292
00:22:17,869 --> 00:22:21,566
[Crowd Yelling]

293
00:22:23,675 --> 00:22:25,643
[Shouting, Indistinct]

294
00:22:25,744 --> 00:22:28,440
No, no, no, no! Get away!

295
00:22:28,547 --> 00:22:32,074
- [Whistle Blows]
- Your job is to clear this scum away...

296
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,277
- and let my factory get back to work.
- What can we do?

297
00:22:34,386 --> 00:22:36,445
That's your job! Scum!

298
00:22:39,658 --> 00:22:42,422
- Go!
- But they're just trying
to feed their families, Papa.

299
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:44,427
- What?
- The workers.

300
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:45,757
Scum!

301
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,456
Scum!

302
00:22:51,103 --> 00:22:54,231
Manolo, when push comes to shove...

303
00:22:54,339 --> 00:22:56,773
a man has only one duty...

304
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:59,105
and that is to choose the winning side.

305
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,542
Eh?

306
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:05,814
- Come on.
- [Whistle Blows]

307
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:16,785
<i>[Man On P.A. Speaking Spanish]</i>

308
00:23:29,541 --> 00:23:31,475
- Hi.
- Hi.

309
00:23:33,278 --> 00:23:35,212
- Good to see you.
- You too.

310
00:23:35,313 --> 00:23:37,747
- [Horn Honking]
- Nice car.

311
00:23:46,858 --> 00:23:48,826
[Leila]
Where did you get all this?

312
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:50,918
<i>They're my dad's files from the '50s.</i>

313
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:52,929
There's more at the hotel.

314
00:23:53,031 --> 00:23:56,432
- He actually sent this stuff to you?
- Yeah.

315
00:23:56,535 --> 00:23:59,095
<i>You are making progress.</i>

316
00:23:59,204 --> 00:24:01,604
What's the reason for the change?

317
00:24:01,706 --> 00:24:04,869
I don't know.
I'm almost scared to find out.

318
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:14,009
<i>"Foundation for the Sick."</i>

319
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:16,383
God, such a different world.

320
00:24:18,757 --> 00:24:22,420
<i>[Manolo Narrating] Josemaría wrote to me
once a year until he died.</i>

321
00:24:22,527 --> 00:24:26,190
<i>I never wrote back,
but he kept writing anyway.</i>

322
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:30,792
<i>In his letters he told me
the turns his life was taking.</i>

323
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:33,334
Honorio.

324
00:24:33,438 --> 00:24:35,065
[Honorio Gasping]

325
00:24:35,173 --> 00:24:36,663
Josemaría.

326
00:24:37,776 --> 00:24:39,801
Oh, look at you.

327
00:24:39,911 --> 00:24:41,378
Give me your hand.

328
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:44,373
How's my old employer?

329
00:24:44,483 --> 00:24:46,576
Papa died four years ago, Honorio.

330
00:24:46,685 --> 00:24:48,380
Ah.

331
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:50,887
I said my first Mass for him.

332
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:56,017
Do you- you remember...
[Labored Breathing]

333
00:24:56,127 --> 00:24:58,322
The chocolate bean?

334
00:24:58,430 --> 00:24:59,988
Of course.

335
00:25:00,098 --> 00:25:02,066
It was a great lesson.

336
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:05,466
[Laughing, Coughing]

337
00:25:05,570 --> 00:25:09,165
[Gasping]

338
00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:13,411
I'm sorry. That won't work.

339
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:15,036
Why not?

340
00:25:16,615 --> 00:25:18,207
Because...

341
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:19,783
I'm Jewish.

342
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,223
You know, the love of my life is Jewish.

343
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:36,297
Once I thought of conversion...

344
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:42,572
but I couldn't dishonor my father.

345
00:25:42,674 --> 00:25:47,907
Honoring our parents is the sweetest precept
of all, Honorio, and very dear to God.

346
00:25:48,013 --> 00:25:50,982
- But Jesus Christ-
- Then he won't turn his back on me...

347
00:25:51,082 --> 00:25:53,209
when I stand before him, will he?

348
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:56,280
What I know for sure is that...

349
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,288
he loves you very much.

350
00:26:03,194 --> 00:26:04,718
Thank you.

351
00:26:07,265 --> 00:26:10,257
I was afraid of dying here alone.

352
00:26:13,772 --> 00:26:15,569
[Breathing Heavily]

353
00:26:17,375 --> 00:26:20,708
Please pray with me, Father.

354
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:25,181
- [Saying Prayer In Hebrew]
- And you shall love the Lord your God...

355
00:26:25,283 --> 00:26:27,342
with all your heart...

356
00:26:27,452 --> 00:26:29,352
and with all your mind...

357
00:26:29,454 --> 00:26:31,422
and with all your soul.

358
00:26:32,524 --> 00:26:34,151
Our Father...

359
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,090
who art in heaven...

360
00:26:36,194 --> 00:26:38,162
hallowed be thy name.

361
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:41,426
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done on earth...

362
00:26:41,533 --> 00:26:43,501
as it is in heaven.

363
00:26:57,649 --> 00:26:59,617
Good night, Father.

364
00:27:14,065 --> 00:27:16,761
- [Josemaría] Lord, open my eyes.
- [Scribbling]

365
00:27:16,868 --> 00:27:19,359
I am such a blind donkey.

366
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:25,405
For so long I have felt you
guiding me, but to what?

367
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:27,535
[Scribbling Continues]

368
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:30,114
Do you have a purpose
for your donkey, Lord...

369
00:27:30,215 --> 00:27:32,342
but I'm too blind to see it?

370
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:39,790
You were there tonight, Lord.

371
00:27:39,891 --> 00:27:41,859
I felt you there.

372
00:27:42,894 --> 00:27:44,862
Please be with me now.

373
00:27:46,898 --> 00:27:48,627
Please show me.

374
00:28:18,096 --> 00:28:20,792
<i>[Honorio's Voice]
Ah, now, look at this.</i>

375
00:28:20,899 --> 00:28:24,164
<i>Just a poor, ordinary little bean.</i>

376
00:28:41,519 --> 00:28:43,544
<i>Patience, skill...</i>

377
00:28:43,655 --> 00:28:46,453
<i>hard work and love...</i>

378
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:51,086
<i>can unleash the divine flavors hidden within.</i>

379
00:29:11,983 --> 00:29:13,951
<i>Do you understand the lesson?</i>

380
00:29:16,054 --> 00:29:18,147
<i>[Chuckling]</i>

381
00:29:19,491 --> 00:29:22,460
[Squeaking]

382
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:33,403
Yes.

383
00:29:33,505 --> 00:29:35,405
Yes, I see.

384
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:37,475
Everyone and everything.

385
00:29:37,575 --> 00:29:39,042
Everyone and everything.

386
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:47,842
Everyone and everything...

387
00:29:47,952 --> 00:29:50,318
for your glory.

388
00:29:52,957 --> 00:29:56,916
Your arms open to all.

389
00:29:57,929 --> 00:29:59,760
One by one.

390
00:30:02,867 --> 00:30:05,563
- Thank you, Lord.
- [Birds Chirping]

391
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:09,471
So this group of red-blooded
young men are prepared...

392
00:30:09,574 --> 00:30:12,543
to offer themselves completely to God...

393
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:17,172
in, uh, apostolic work, including celibacy?

394
00:30:17,282 --> 00:30:19,045
Yes, Vicar.

395
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,675
That was the choice I gave them
and one they accepted.

396
00:30:21,786 --> 00:30:23,583
- Really?
- Yes.

397
00:30:23,688 --> 00:30:26,657
[Birds Chirping, Tweeting]

398
00:30:28,359 --> 00:30:29,826
How many?

399
00:30:30,995 --> 00:30:32,326
Uh...

400
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:33,727
three.

401
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,231
Three.

402
00:30:38,303 --> 00:30:40,066
[Laughs]

403
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:46,042
<i>[Vicar's Voice] My worry
is that this calling may be delusional.</i>

404
00:30:47,412 --> 00:30:49,778
[Chattering]

405
00:30:57,689 --> 00:31:00,681
<i>[Man]
And this work is to include women?</i>

406
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:02,555
Yes, Your Excellency.

407
00:31:02,660 --> 00:31:05,993
They will live separately,
but our work will include them...

408
00:31:06,097 --> 00:31:09,294
and will also be open to married people.

409
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:11,095
[Sighs]

410
00:31:11,202 --> 00:31:13,432
Living in the same institution?

411
00:31:13,538 --> 00:31:15,802
It's not an institution or a movement.

412
00:31:15,907 --> 00:31:18,774
It's just a family of individuals.

413
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:21,971
And no, married couples will live at home.

414
00:31:23,448 --> 00:31:27,248
[Sighs]
It all seems rather...

415
00:31:28,686 --> 00:31:30,051
Protestant-

416
00:31:31,823 --> 00:31:34,849
that God is to be found in the...

417
00:31:34,959 --> 00:31:37,086
well, vanities of daily life.

418
00:31:37,195 --> 00:31:38,662
Hmm?

419
00:31:38,763 --> 00:31:42,324
Outside holy orders.

420
00:31:43,234 --> 00:31:45,168
No vows. Hmm?

421
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:47,864
No... habits.

422
00:31:49,507 --> 00:31:53,841
Well, Jesus spent most
of his life working in a shop...

423
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:55,503
in Nazareth.

424
00:31:57,315 --> 00:31:59,840
God's world is so full of, uh-

425
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:09,584
[Church Bells Tolling]

426
00:32:11,062 --> 00:32:13,121
[People Chattering In Distance]

427
00:32:15,033 --> 00:32:17,001
God's world is so full of goodness.

428
00:32:18,503 --> 00:32:22,667
If we do them for love,
each daily task can give him glory.

429
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:26,972
Small but regular acts of love
between husbands and wives...

430
00:32:27,078 --> 00:32:29,706
between friends, between strangers...

431
00:32:29,814 --> 00:32:33,215
each revealing the beauty of his creation.

432
00:32:34,585 --> 00:32:39,522
And you want to open
a new residence in Valencia, huh?

433
00:32:39,624 --> 00:32:42,889
Yes. And one day in New York, Paris...

434
00:32:42,994 --> 00:32:46,054
London and-and... Tokyo.
[Laughs]

435
00:32:46,164 --> 00:32:48,598
It's a long way to Tokyo.

436
00:32:50,234 --> 00:32:52,566
And, uh...

437
00:32:56,174 --> 00:32:58,802
no money yet to speak of.

438
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:05,044
Well, I can't provide any.

439
00:33:05,149 --> 00:33:07,674
No, I didn't come to ask for that.

440
00:33:07,785 --> 00:33:11,949
I ask merely for your permission-
for me and for the work.

441
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:18,952
And you shall have them.

442
00:33:19,797 --> 00:33:23,096
Father Escrivá...

443
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:27,160
I offer you a job as my secretary.

444
00:33:27,271 --> 00:33:29,262
In time this will lead to a career...

445
00:33:29,374 --> 00:33:32,468
that might grant you the influence
that you would need...

446
00:33:32,577 --> 00:33:36,104
to realize this- this dream of yours.

447
00:33:36,214 --> 00:33:38,808
So, what do you say?

448
00:33:40,051 --> 00:33:41,416
I said no, thank you.

449
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,577
Santi.

450
00:33:44,355 --> 00:33:46,255
Now, it won't be easy, I know.

451
00:33:46,357 --> 00:33:50,123
But I'll always see that there's a roof
over your heads and food on the table.

452
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:52,059
No? Huh?

453
00:33:52,163 --> 00:33:54,358
- Josemaría-
- Actually...

454
00:33:54,465 --> 00:33:56,228
I have an idea.

455
00:33:56,334 --> 00:34:02,603
<i>[Children]
Pecunia in arboribus non crescit.</i>

456
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:05,608
<i>Crescit. Good. Okay. Agustin.</i>

457
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:08,144
<i>Pec- Pec-</i>

458
00:34:08,246 --> 00:34:10,146
<i>- Pecunia.
- I can't do it, sir.</i>

459
00:34:10,248 --> 00:34:12,808
- [Other Children Laugh]
- Yes, you can. Shh, shh. Yes, you can.

460
00:34:12,917 --> 00:34:14,976
You will learn, and I will learn to teach it.

461
00:34:15,086 --> 00:34:17,486
[Coughing]

462
00:34:17,588 --> 00:34:19,055
Oh, no. Damn it!

463
00:34:19,157 --> 00:34:20,624
Stay here.

464
00:34:24,262 --> 00:34:26,093
- [Water Running]
- [Man Coughs]

465
00:34:26,197 --> 00:34:28,358
[Groans]
I'm sorry, Father.

466
00:34:28,466 --> 00:34:31,094
Sorry. But I can't-

467
00:34:31,202 --> 00:34:33,727
The smell. I can't.

468
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:36,466
- [Laughing]
- [Coughing]

469
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:38,667
[Coughing Continues]

470
00:34:38,776 --> 00:34:40,243
How's your Latin?

471
00:34:41,512 --> 00:34:42,809
Go.

472
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:44,381
[Man] No.

473
00:34:46,984 --> 00:34:48,417
Go on. Go.

474
00:34:48,519 --> 00:34:50,783
- Go, go, go. Go.
- [Laughing]

475
00:34:53,224 --> 00:34:55,454
- [Dog Barking]
- [Crowd Chattering]

476
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:58,688
- [Horn Honking]
- [Manolo] Union scum.

477
00:34:58,796 --> 00:35:00,286
Drive through them!

478
00:35:01,199 --> 00:35:02,757
Don't. Thugs.

479
00:35:02,867 --> 00:35:05,062
How can you do this?
You know my father's ill.

480
00:35:05,169 --> 00:35:06,966
Then God is just.

481
00:35:07,071 --> 00:35:10,598
- [Yelling]
- [Whistle Blows]

482
00:35:15,746 --> 00:35:19,238
Damn unions.
I've always said they're going to kill him.

483
00:35:19,350 --> 00:35:22,513
[Woman]
It's a stroke. The doctor just left.

484
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:25,350
[Manolo]
No. No.

485
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:31,386
Papa.

486
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:35,625
[Wheezing]

487
00:35:35,733 --> 00:35:37,792
Papa.

488
00:35:37,902 --> 00:35:39,426
[Nurse]
He can't speak.

489
00:35:39,537 --> 00:35:43,132
What? What did the doctor say?

490
00:35:43,241 --> 00:35:45,675
That it's God's will.

491
00:35:45,776 --> 00:35:47,209
Get out of here.

492
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:49,074
Manolo, please.

493
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:50,647
Get out of here.

494
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:52,949
Get out!

495
00:35:53,050 --> 00:35:54,517
Get out!

496
00:36:04,295 --> 00:36:07,355
[Wheezing]

497
00:36:07,465 --> 00:36:08,989
Papa.

498
00:36:11,369 --> 00:36:13,132
Papa?

499
00:36:17,975 --> 00:36:19,465
Papa.

500
00:36:22,780 --> 00:36:26,580
## [Piano]

501
00:36:44,302 --> 00:36:45,769
Thank you.

502
00:37:00,651 --> 00:37:02,551
Good afternoon, brother.

503
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:04,710
Brother?

504
00:37:04,822 --> 00:37:06,653
Uh, Josemaría.

505
00:37:07,925 --> 00:37:10,519
I know who you are, Josemaría.

506
00:37:15,266 --> 00:37:17,530
[Clears Throat]

507
00:37:17,635 --> 00:37:20,604
I heard your sad news, Manolo.

508
00:37:20,705 --> 00:37:22,730
You have been in my prayers.

509
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:26,867
Thank you.
But I don't need your brand of sympathy-

510
00:37:26,978 --> 00:37:28,468
however sincere.

511
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:31,275
Manolo,
whatever struggles you are experiencing-

512
00:37:31,382 --> 00:37:35,079
- Struggles?
- Well, whatever doubts you may be having.

513
00:37:35,186 --> 00:37:38,155
Doubts. Struggles.

514
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:42,818
Josemaría, I blundered into the seminary
in deference to my mother.

515
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:45,657
I left because I wasn't priest material.

516
00:37:46,697 --> 00:37:48,961
As you know.

517
00:37:49,066 --> 00:37:53,002
Well, maybe not, but it doesn't mean
you're not saint material.

518
00:37:53,738 --> 00:37:55,103
[Chuckles]

519
00:37:57,375 --> 00:37:59,536
You know...

520
00:37:59,644 --> 00:38:04,047
my recurring nightmare
is that I was partly to blame for you leaving.

521
00:38:04,148 --> 00:38:06,309
No, Josemaría.

522
00:38:06,417 --> 00:38:09,215
Unlike you,
I chose to live in the real world.

523
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:12,050
But I appreciate your concern.

524
00:38:12,156 --> 00:38:13,521
It's not concern, Manolo.

525
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:18,160
It's love.

526
00:38:18,262 --> 00:38:21,663
Our Lord said love,
and love is what he meant.

527
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:24,462
And it's what we owe each other. No?

528
00:38:26,237 --> 00:38:28,603
Josemaría, the truth is...

529
00:38:28,706 --> 00:38:31,436
we are born alone and we die alone.

530
00:38:31,542 --> 00:38:34,705
All we have in between
is a battle I intend to win.

531
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:37,474
The rest is, frankly, sentimental drivel.

532
00:38:38,749 --> 00:38:41,877
- ## [Resumes]
- Well, I will leave you.

533
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:44,686
Call on me.

534
00:38:46,257 --> 00:38:47,724
I'll come, I promise.

535
00:38:50,861 --> 00:38:53,830
Josemaría. You don't give up, do you?

536
00:38:53,931 --> 00:38:56,923
It may help you to find some meaning
for your suffering, Manolo.

537
00:38:57,034 --> 00:39:00,595
Suffering has no meaning. It's meaningless.

538
00:39:00,705 --> 00:39:02,969
If you can show me otherwise,
I'll kiss your ass.

539
00:39:03,074 --> 00:39:04,541
<i>That's my promise.</i>

540
00:39:05,676 --> 00:39:08,144
I know what it is to be angry at life.

541
00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:12,778
Please be careful
where that leads you, Manolo.

542
00:39:14,952 --> 00:39:15,714
Sheep.

543
00:39:42,313 --> 00:39:46,306
<i>[Manolo Narrating] Around the time
that Josemaría got a call from God...</i>

544
00:39:46,417 --> 00:39:48,681
<i>I also got a call-</i>

545
00:39:48,786 --> 00:39:52,119
<i>from an old friend of my father's.</i>

546
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:54,157
Ah, Torres.

547
00:39:54,258 --> 00:39:57,056
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

548
00:39:57,161 --> 00:40:00,130
## [Soldiers Singing In Spanish]

549
00:40:05,669 --> 00:40:07,899
- Well?
- A spy?

550
00:40:08,005 --> 00:40:09,734
Yes. You.

551
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:11,569
But I expected something more.

552
00:40:11,675 --> 00:40:15,236
With the king gone,
Spain has lost its center of gravity.

553
00:40:15,346 --> 00:40:18,645
Which we will now re-create,
by force if needs be.

554
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:20,512
<i>[Man #2]
And other means.</i>

555
00:40:20,618 --> 00:40:22,984
But our government's elected. It's popular.

556
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:24,281
Its time is over.

557
00:40:24,388 --> 00:40:26,015
<i>[Man #1]
The government is a rotten biscuit.</i>

558
00:40:26,123 --> 00:40:28,990
- Tap it and see the maggots emerge.
- Maggots?

559
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:31,118
Socialists who want a socialist state.

560
00:40:31,228 --> 00:40:33,128
Stalinists who want a Stalinist state.

561
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:35,095
Anarchists who want no state at all.

562
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:38,134
Manolo, we want to create a new Spain.

563
00:40:38,235 --> 00:40:40,897
<i>- [Man #1] A united Spain.
- Cleansed with blood if necessary.</i>

564
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:43,803
<i>[Man #1]
Resurrected, great and as it once was-</i>

565
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:45,671
<i>- ordered, vigorous.
- [Man #2] And admired.</i>

566
00:40:45,776 --> 00:40:48,540
- [Pounding On Table]
- [Speaking German]

567
00:40:52,316 --> 00:40:55,547
## [Singing In Spanish]

568
00:41:00,191 --> 00:41:02,625
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
They called us fascists.</i>

569
00:41:02,726 --> 00:41:05,456
<i>- We called them communists.
- ## [March]</i>

570
00:41:05,563 --> 00:41:09,499
<i>Really, the world was much
more complicated than that.</i>

571
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:12,569
<i>But many preferred to see it
in those simple terms.</i>

572
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:16,970
<i>Three years later,
half a million people were dead-</i>

573
00:41:17,074 --> 00:41:19,634
<i>most of them civilians.</i>

574
00:41:19,743 --> 00:41:22,075
<i>But even in times like these...</i>

575
00:41:22,179 --> 00:41:27,048
<i>some people are more interested
in hats and shoes.</i>

576
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:35,250
[Mother]
I thought you were going to buy new shoes.

577
00:41:35,359 --> 00:41:40,319
Uh, yes, I was, but, uh,
something else came up.

578
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:45,095
- What was that?
- No. L- I met an old lady who-

579
00:41:45,202 --> 00:41:47,067
<i>- Who needed a hat.
- [Man #2] And some breakfast?</i>

580
00:41:47,171 --> 00:41:49,332
<i>- [Man #1] Yes, and some lunch.
- Thank you.</i>

581
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:50,771
[Chuckling]

582
00:41:50,875 --> 00:41:53,844
Sit down, please, Pedro, Isidoro.

583
00:41:53,944 --> 00:41:55,468
Well, uh-

584
00:41:57,515 --> 00:41:59,210
- So?
- [Clears Throat]

585
00:41:59,316 --> 00:42:02,945
This group that keeps you from your homes-
what is it called?

586
00:42:03,053 --> 00:42:04,884
We don't have a name, Mama.

587
00:42:04,989 --> 00:42:06,718
We just refer to it as God's work.

588
00:42:07,725 --> 00:42:09,420
Latin would sound better.

589
00:42:10,494 --> 00:42:13,588
<i>Uh, Opus Dei.</i>

590
00:42:17,568 --> 00:42:20,036
<i>##[Radio... Guitar]</i>

591
00:42:21,672 --> 00:42:23,697
<i>[Volume Increases]</i>

592
00:42:23,807 --> 00:42:26,776
<i>##[Folk Chorus Singing In Spanish]</i>

593
00:42:32,483 --> 00:42:35,247
Well, your donkey may lack funds...

594
00:42:35,352 --> 00:42:37,320
but the work has found its name.

595
00:42:40,090 --> 00:42:41,489
[Chuckling]
What's next?

596
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:51,501
<i>##[Chorus Singing In Spanish]</i>

597
00:43:00,544 --> 00:43:02,375
[Chattering, Cheering]

598
00:43:02,479 --> 00:43:03,969
<i>Vamos.</i>

599
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:09,352
<i>Está bien.</i>

600
00:43:11,121 --> 00:43:15,785
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
A communist strike killed my father.</i>

601
00:43:15,893 --> 00:43:18,760
<i>Now it was my turn to strike.</i>

602
00:43:18,862 --> 00:43:20,955
<i>##[Continues]</i>

603
00:43:29,239 --> 00:43:31,298
- [Man Grunting]
- Get out of the car!

604
00:43:31,408 --> 00:43:33,808
- Come here, scum!
- [Man Shouts]

605
00:43:34,745 --> 00:43:37,145
- Put the hood on him!
- Please! No!

606
00:43:37,247 --> 00:43:38,714
[Muffled Shouting]

607
00:43:38,816 --> 00:43:41,785
Yeah, we'll show you how just God is.

608
00:43:41,885 --> 00:43:44,183
- In the boss's car.
- [Muffled Screaming]

609
00:43:45,656 --> 00:43:47,487
Let's go!

610
00:44:04,308 --> 00:44:06,640
[Car Doors Open, Close]

611
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:20,017
[Whimpering]

612
00:44:21,625 --> 00:44:23,718
Where's your gun?

613
00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:25,727
This is not a game.

614
00:44:25,829 --> 00:44:28,559
He killed your father.

615
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:32,166
Ah, damn it.
The bastard's shitting his pants.

616
00:44:32,269 --> 00:44:34,362
- [Whimpering]
- Do it.

617
00:44:34,471 --> 00:44:37,065
[Muffled Screaming]

618
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:39,233
Do it, damn it.

619
00:44:51,588 --> 00:44:53,055
[Engine Starts]

620
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:04,694
Pedro.

621
00:45:04,802 --> 00:45:06,997
- [Laughs] You're crazy.
- No, I'm not.

622
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:08,901
You're crazy.

623
00:45:09,006 --> 00:45:10,701
He'll hate the whole idea.

624
00:45:10,808 --> 00:45:12,708
Well, let's ask him.

625
00:45:12,810 --> 00:45:14,209
Ask me?

626
00:45:14,311 --> 00:45:16,575
This. We're gonna put them up
all over Madrid.

627
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,204
Look.

628
00:45:19,650 --> 00:45:20,878
[Pedro]
Not me, Father. Not me.

629
00:45:20,984 --> 00:45:23,714
- A crusade?
- Yes, Father.

630
00:45:23,821 --> 00:45:27,780
Using the cross to incite hatred and anger-
that's Christian?

631
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:29,415
Well, maybe not.

632
00:45:29,526 --> 00:45:32,222
But, Father, the government
is openly attacking the church.

633
00:45:32,329 --> 00:45:34,263
No, it isn't.
It's trying to modernize Spain.

634
00:45:34,364 --> 00:45:35,831
Come on, Pedro.

635
00:45:35,933 --> 00:45:37,798
If we don't do something,
we are just cowards.

636
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:39,334
- Or worse- traitors.
- Traitors.

637
00:45:39,436 --> 00:45:41,233
- Traitors?
- Yes, Paco. Traitors.

638
00:45:41,338 --> 00:45:42,771
That's what people are saying.

639
00:45:42,873 --> 00:45:45,171
Standing by while the church gets attacked-

640
00:45:45,275 --> 00:45:47,300
how is that being a good Catholic?

641
00:45:47,411 --> 00:45:50,346
Pedro, is it understandable
to want to protect the church?

642
00:45:50,447 --> 00:45:51,573
Yes, Father, but-

643
00:45:51,682 --> 00:45:54,412
Juan, is it understandable
to want social justice?

644
00:45:54,518 --> 00:45:55,678
Yes, of course.

645
00:45:55,786 --> 00:45:58,346
Good. So the question is,
how do we achieve both?

646
00:45:58,455 --> 00:45:59,752
[Mother]
By feeding the hungry.

647
00:45:59,857 --> 00:46:02,985
And lunch is ready, so sit down now.

648
00:46:07,464 --> 00:46:09,796
So we just let the matter drop?

649
00:46:09,900 --> 00:46:11,390
No.

650
00:46:11,502 --> 00:46:14,164
Look, I'm not going
to tell you what to think.

651
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:17,365
God gave each of you a brain
and reason and a conscience.

652
00:46:17,474 --> 00:46:20,375
Why? So that you can
come to conclusions on your own...

653
00:46:20,477 --> 00:46:22,877
and take personal responsibility for them.

654
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:27,508
But before rushing to act-

655
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:30,314
before trying to change the world-

656
00:46:30,420 --> 00:46:32,786
first think about changing yourselves.

657
00:46:34,491 --> 00:46:38,018
We're building something vital here together.

658
00:46:38,128 --> 00:46:40,119
Now- especially now-

659
00:46:40,230 --> 00:46:43,495
we have to be sowers of peace and joy.

660
00:46:46,270 --> 00:46:48,170
And lunch, Mama.

661
00:46:51,508 --> 00:46:54,238
- Father!
- [Loud Clatter]

662
00:46:54,344 --> 00:46:56,039
They've started killing priests.

663
00:46:56,146 --> 00:46:59,377
- What?
- It's in the newspaper.

664
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:00,848
[Paco]
Oh, my God.

665
00:47:00,951 --> 00:47:03,146
- Where?
- Here in Madrid.

666
00:47:03,253 --> 00:47:05,312
Let me see.

667
00:47:07,758 --> 00:47:10,249
So, what do we do now, Father?

668
00:47:10,360 --> 00:47:12,487
Exactly what I just said, Juan.

669
00:47:14,198 --> 00:47:15,722
Please.

670
00:47:18,802 --> 00:47:21,635
Bless us, O Lord, and these thy gifts...

671
00:47:21,738 --> 00:47:23,171
which we are about to receive...

672
00:47:23,273 --> 00:47:25,901
from your bounty, through Christ our Lord.

673
00:47:26,009 --> 00:47:28,034
- Amen.
- [Others] Amen.

674
00:47:33,684 --> 00:47:35,618
[Crowd Shouting]

675
00:47:50,500 --> 00:47:52,559
[Shouting, Cheering]

676
00:47:59,676 --> 00:48:02,201
[Bell Clanging]

677
00:48:04,581 --> 00:48:06,105
[Man]
Oh, what have we here?

678
00:48:06,216 --> 00:48:07,240
Found a cockroach.

679
00:48:07,351 --> 00:48:08,511
Hey, watch where you're going.

680
00:48:08,619 --> 00:48:10,086
How about we squash it, eh?

681
00:48:10,187 --> 00:48:11,984
- [Muttering]
- Let's squash him.

682
00:48:14,291 --> 00:48:16,486
[Man]
Well, well, well.

683
00:48:16,593 --> 00:48:18,652
- Priest.
- What have we got here?

684
00:48:20,297 --> 00:48:21,764
- A little priest?
- Oh, yeah.

685
00:48:21,865 --> 00:48:23,457
- Whoa!
- Look there.

686
00:48:23,567 --> 00:48:25,034
- I'm sorry.
- What's he carrying?

687
00:48:25,135 --> 00:48:27,569
So, what have we got there? Huh?

688
00:48:27,671 --> 00:48:30,333
- Come on. Show us.
- No, no. Please. Please.

689
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:33,773
Give me the packet,
or I stick you with this.

690
00:48:33,877 --> 00:48:35,367
[Woman]
Stab the parasite.

691
00:48:35,479 --> 00:48:37,674
I'm not a parasite.

692
00:48:37,781 --> 00:48:39,612
I have to work for a living,
just like all of you.

693
00:48:39,716 --> 00:48:42,082
Work for a living?
You know what working for a living is?

694
00:48:42,686 --> 00:48:44,176
That's enough!

695
00:48:44,288 --> 00:48:47,451
- That's enough!
- [Shouting, Muttering]

696
00:48:47,557 --> 00:48:50,720
Please! Get on the next one.

697
00:48:50,827 --> 00:48:52,624
- Relax.
- [All Muttering]

698
00:48:52,729 --> 00:48:54,128
- Relax, old man.
- Please.

699
00:48:54,231 --> 00:48:55,562
See you later, priest.

700
00:48:55,666 --> 00:48:57,634
- I'm on your side.
- Fascist.

701
00:48:57,734 --> 00:49:00,100
- [Muttering, Laughing]
- Come on.

702
00:49:00,203 --> 00:49:02,194
- We'll get you next time.
- Yeah.

703
00:49:08,111 --> 00:49:10,841
[Whistle Blows]

704
00:49:15,319 --> 00:49:20,052
They've got a thing
against enemies of their class.

705
00:49:20,157 --> 00:49:22,523
- Can't say I blame them.
- No. I know.

706
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:25,959
All part of creating
this new, more civilized Spain.

707
00:49:26,063 --> 00:49:27,462
Exactly.

708
00:49:27,564 --> 00:49:29,964
And how will uncivilized behavior
accomplish that?

709
00:49:30,067 --> 00:49:32,331
Can't make an omelet without breaking eggs.

710
00:49:32,436 --> 00:49:34,267
No. Life is not an omelet.

711
00:49:34,371 --> 00:49:36,168
And people are not eggs.

712
00:49:36,273 --> 00:49:40,369
Okay. Hey, if I was you...

713
00:49:40,477 --> 00:49:43,913
I'd stop wandering about
in that costume of yours.

714
00:49:44,014 --> 00:49:45,845
It won't protect you anymore.

715
00:49:45,949 --> 00:49:48,315
I don't wear this for protection.

716
00:49:48,418 --> 00:49:51,478
You got balls for a bourgeois ass.

717
00:49:55,625 --> 00:49:58,025
[Boy]
One, two. One, two.

718
00:49:58,128 --> 00:50:00,255
One, two. One, two.

719
00:50:00,364 --> 00:50:02,764
One, two. One, two.

720
00:50:02,866 --> 00:50:05,494
One, two. One, two.

721
00:50:05,602 --> 00:50:06,694
Thank you, Father.

722
00:50:06,803 --> 00:50:08,270
One, two. Halt.

723
00:50:08,372 --> 00:50:10,806
[Cheering, Singing]

724
00:50:10,907 --> 00:50:13,000
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
From their palaces, the bishops said...</i>

725
00:50:13,110 --> 00:50:15,806
<i>"The meek shall inherit the earth."</i>

726
00:50:17,481 --> 00:50:18,709
Ready!

727
00:50:19,649 --> 00:50:21,207
Aim! Fire!

728
00:50:21,318 --> 00:50:22,615
- [Lmitating Gunshots]
- [Groans]

729
00:50:22,719 --> 00:50:25,916
- [Man] Hey!
- [Children Laughing]

730
00:50:28,658 --> 00:50:30,922
<i>But the meek were tired of waiting.</i>

731
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:32,393
- [Groans]
- [Children Laughing]

732
00:50:34,798 --> 00:50:37,733
<i>They took the bishops and their palaces.</i>

733
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:41,030
<i>He was lucky it was only a rock.</i>

734
00:50:47,310 --> 00:50:48,607
Hello?

735
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:53,279
Juan? Paco?

736
00:50:58,221 --> 00:51:00,246
Happy birthday!

737
00:51:00,357 --> 00:51:02,587
[All Exclaiming, Laughing]

738
00:51:04,027 --> 00:51:05,551
It's not my birthday.

739
00:51:05,662 --> 00:51:08,392
Please. Come on.

740
00:51:08,498 --> 00:51:09,624
Josemaría...

741
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:11,360
as your brother, I have been chosen...

742
00:51:11,468 --> 00:51:14,995
to ask you to celebrate
our second year together...

743
00:51:15,105 --> 00:51:16,572
by removing your shoes.

744
00:51:16,673 --> 00:51:18,106
- [All Laughing]
- Yes, Father!

745
00:51:18,208 --> 00:51:20,176
- Take them off.
- Take off your shoes.

746
00:51:20,277 --> 00:51:23,144
- Shoes off. Come on, Father.
- No.

747
00:51:23,246 --> 00:51:24,838
- Yes.
- Yes.

748
00:51:24,948 --> 00:51:27,041
- The shoes.
- Take them off.

749
00:51:28,285 --> 00:51:30,276
[All Chuckling]

750
00:51:31,354 --> 00:51:35,017
- Behold a simple shoe.
- [All Murmur]

751
00:51:35,125 --> 00:51:36,683
But is it what it seems?

752
00:51:36,793 --> 00:51:37,782
- Yes.
- Yes.

753
00:51:37,894 --> 00:51:42,695
No. It is, in fact, a hole.

754
00:51:42,799 --> 00:51:44,130
[All Laughing]

755
00:51:44,234 --> 00:51:45,929
A hole masquerading as a shoe.

756
00:51:46,036 --> 00:51:47,469
Oh!

757
00:51:47,571 --> 00:51:50,267
And a hole surrounded by leather.

758
00:51:51,608 --> 00:51:53,007
[Laughing Continues]

759
00:51:53,110 --> 00:51:54,771
Shh! Shh!

760
00:51:54,878 --> 00:51:59,440
<i>But also a testament
to 20 kilometers a day...</i>

761
00:51:59,549 --> 00:52:01,312
seven days a week...

762
00:52:01,418 --> 00:52:03,852
rain and shine.

763
00:52:05,055 --> 00:52:06,488
- Yes!
- Thank you.

764
00:52:06,590 --> 00:52:10,424
And in pity for this innocent shoe...

765
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:13,621
we have also pooled together for-

766
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:15,163
- Ta-da!
- [All Cheering]

767
00:52:15,265 --> 00:52:18,291
- [Man] What nice shoes.
- Try them on.

768
00:52:18,401 --> 00:52:21,370
- [Gunshot]
- [Pedro] Get down! Get down!

769
00:52:22,372 --> 00:52:23,839
[Mother]
Santiago, get down!

770
00:52:23,940 --> 00:52:25,032
- Santi!
- God!

771
00:52:25,142 --> 00:52:28,134
[Gunshots]

772
00:52:28,245 --> 00:52:30,213
Get down!

773
00:52:30,313 --> 00:52:32,907
[Gunshots Continue Outside]

774
00:52:33,016 --> 00:52:35,246
<i>[Male Announcer]
This is an announcement
from your government.</i>

775
00:52:35,352 --> 00:52:37,547
<i>There has been a military uprising.</i>

776
00:52:37,654 --> 00:52:41,522
<i>The army has recruited
the Spanish colonial army of Morocco.</i>

777
00:52:41,625 --> 00:52:44,389
<i>All able-bodied Spaniards
who love their country-</i>

778
00:52:44,628 --> 00:52:47,688
[Clock Ticking]

779
00:52:54,871 --> 00:52:58,238
<i>[Manolo Narrating]
It's remarkably easy to join a war.</i>

780
00:52:58,341 --> 00:53:00,241
[Shouting, Cheering]

781
00:53:00,343 --> 00:53:03,005
<i>I wormed my way into a communist brigade.</i>

782
00:53:03,113 --> 00:53:08,983
<i>- ## [Singing In Spanish]
- So far, I was enjoying being a spy.</i>

783
00:53:09,085 --> 00:53:12,350
<i>There's something inspiring
about the common purpose...</i>

784
00:53:12,455 --> 00:53:14,946
<i>even when it's not yours.</i>

785
00:53:15,058 --> 00:53:18,619
<i>I can't describe that ecstasy
of belonging to a crowd-</i>

786
00:53:18,728 --> 00:53:21,162
<i>even when it's the enemy.</i>

787
00:53:21,264 --> 00:53:23,732
<i>There's no better feeling.</i>

788
00:53:23,833 --> 00:53:26,700
<i>Well, apart from one.</i>

789
00:53:41,017 --> 00:53:42,814
Cat got your tongue, comrade?

790
00:53:47,390 --> 00:53:50,450
## [Singing Continues]

791
00:53:59,603 --> 00:54:02,470
[Crowd Applauding, Cheering]

792
00:54:08,011 --> 00:54:10,411
[Microphone Feedback]

793
00:54:11,514 --> 00:54:13,812
[Man]
So many young people-

794
00:54:13,917 --> 00:54:16,613
what do you know of suffering and death?

795
00:54:16,720 --> 00:54:19,211
<i>How they will taunt you- "Is it worth it?"</i>

796
00:54:19,322 --> 00:54:21,984
<i>They will ask again and again,
"Is it worth it?"</i>

797
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:27,792
<i>And what will fill your hearts
with the answer "Yes"? Yes!</i>

798
00:54:29,065 --> 00:54:31,932
- Hatred of oppression? Of tyranny?
- [Crowd] Yes!

799
00:54:32,035 --> 00:54:34,936
- Hatred of those who treat us like animals-
- [Crowd Cheering]

800
00:54:35,038 --> 00:54:38,064
Denying our hopes and stifling our lives?

801
00:54:38,174 --> 00:54:39,266
Yes!

802
00:54:39,376 --> 00:54:41,367
But more.

803
00:54:43,780 --> 00:54:46,510
It will be faith-

804
00:54:46,616 --> 00:54:51,383
faith that a new world will be
born from the blood of the old.

805
00:54:51,488 --> 00:54:52,785
[Cheering]

806
00:54:52,889 --> 00:54:55,722
And comradeship, my brothers and sisters.

807
00:54:57,027 --> 00:54:59,086
And courage-

808
00:54:59,195 --> 00:55:01,220
courage to burst from our cages...

809
00:55:01,331 --> 00:55:03,856
and set ourselves free to live noble...

810
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:06,231
as the eagle hovering
above his mountain peak.

811
00:55:07,570 --> 00:55:10,869
- Or die in the attempt!
- [Cheering]

812
00:55:14,010 --> 00:55:16,478
<i>##[Orchestra On P.A.]</i>

813
00:55:18,148 --> 00:55:23,017
<i>- ##[Chorus Singing..."The Internationale"]
- Thanks.</i>

814
00:55:25,221 --> 00:55:27,519
- Name and country.
- Régis. France.

815
00:55:27,624 --> 00:55:29,854
- Name and country.
- Jan. South Africa.

816
00:55:29,959 --> 00:55:33,360
- Name and country.
- Petofi, lldiko. Hungary, sir.

817
00:55:33,463 --> 00:55:36,557
<i>There are no "sirs" in the Iron Brigade,
lldiko.</i>

818
00:55:36,666 --> 00:55:38,691
Peasants, factory workers...

819
00:55:38,802 --> 00:55:40,770
some like me- escaped convicts.

820
00:55:40,870 --> 00:55:43,566
We are what we are, but we are all equal.

821
00:55:43,673 --> 00:55:45,402
But still fighting to be free-

822
00:55:45,508 --> 00:55:46,805
as we all wish to be!

823
00:55:46,910 --> 00:55:48,901
[Cheering]

824
00:55:49,713 --> 00:55:51,180
Lldiko Petofi.

825
00:55:51,281 --> 00:55:52,578
Yes, sir.

826
00:55:54,184 --> 00:55:56,778
- Oriol.
- Yes, Oriol.

827
00:56:01,624 --> 00:56:02,921
<i>"Yes, Oriol."</i>

828
00:56:06,596 --> 00:56:09,087
- Jealous?
- No.

829
00:56:09,799 --> 00:56:11,733
What is your name?

830
00:56:13,002 --> 00:56:14,299
Manolo.

831
00:56:16,806 --> 00:56:18,296
<i>[Man On P.A.]
Viva la República!</i>

832
00:56:18,408 --> 00:56:20,774
<i>[All]
Vival [Cheering]</i>

833
00:56:24,214 --> 00:56:27,274
[Man Groaning]

834
00:56:27,384 --> 00:56:28,373
[Whistle Blows]

835
00:56:28,485 --> 00:56:29,782
Go, go, go!

836
00:56:37,127 --> 00:56:38,685
[Man Shouts]

837
00:56:45,101 --> 00:56:46,796
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

838
00:56:47,337 --> 00:56:48,929
Come on!

839
00:56:49,038 --> 00:56:50,505
Come on!

840
00:56:54,277 --> 00:56:55,938
Come on!

841
00:56:57,380 --> 00:56:58,904
Come on!

842
00:56:59,716 --> 00:57:00,842
Come on!

843
00:57:03,787 --> 00:57:05,755
[Man Shouts]

844
00:57:13,363 --> 00:57:16,093
Take cover! Move!

845
00:57:16,199 --> 00:57:19,498
[All Shouting]

846
00:57:23,139 --> 00:57:25,039
Fire! Fire! Fire!

847
00:57:32,382 --> 00:57:34,247
[Groans]

848
00:57:39,722 --> 00:57:42,316
Lldi- Ildi- Ildiko!

849
00:57:42,425 --> 00:57:44,518
[Whimpering]

850
00:57:44,627 --> 00:57:47,653
Stop. Go back. Face them.

851
00:57:47,764 --> 00:57:49,698
Thank the bastards for testing your bravery.

852
00:57:56,306 --> 00:57:57,671
Go!

853
00:57:58,508 --> 00:58:00,840
Go! Go. Go.

854
00:58:01,478 --> 00:58:03,002
- Torres.
- Yeah.

855
00:58:03,112 --> 00:58:04,739
Look after her.

856
00:58:07,984 --> 00:58:10,145
[Man]
Forward!

857
00:58:15,492 --> 00:58:17,551
Oh, God. I'm such a coward.

858
00:58:17,660 --> 00:58:19,355
Me too.

859
00:58:37,313 --> 00:58:39,076
I don't feel right about this.

860
00:58:39,182 --> 00:58:40,649
You read the newspapers.

861
00:58:40,750 --> 00:58:43,810
They don't exactly like priests out there,
Father.

862
00:58:43,920 --> 00:58:46,218
Then don't call me Father
when I am dressed like this.

863
00:58:47,824 --> 00:58:49,724
Call me Mariano.

864
00:58:49,826 --> 00:58:52,226
- [Doorbell Buzzing]
- That's Vargas.

865
00:58:52,328 --> 00:58:55,195
Come on, Father. I mean, Mariano.

866
00:59:00,937 --> 00:59:02,996
[Isidoro]
Come on. The car is here.

867
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:06,406
Father, they'll be safe. Don't worry.

